FlowHarvester-bundle.zip
*.spec.bak

docs/config/workstations.yaml.bak

# Local config / asset backups
config/*.bak
config/*.backup

# Developer-local docs (drafts, diagnostic dumps from customer machines,
# screenshots, design notes, …). Tracked docs stay tracked because git
# never ignores already-indexed paths — anything new under docs/ is
# treated as private working-tree noise unless explicitly un-ignored
# below.
docs/*
!docs/customer-install-windows.md
!docs/customer-manual.md
!docs/使用手册.txt
!docs/安装说明.txt
# Don't accidentally swallow nested folders we *do* want tracked in the
# future — by listing the dirs we plan to keep here, the tracking is
# an active choice rather than a `docs/*` accident.
!docs/.gitkeep

# Diagnostic bundles + their unzipped trees
docs/diagnostic_*.zip
docs/diagnostic_*/

# V2 spike artefacts live on the v2-spike branch — on main they're
# only noise (npm node_modules + vite dist + the source tree itself
# all show up as untracked when you ``git checkout main`` after a
# spike build). On v2-spike, the more-specific
# ``extension/node_modules/`` etc. lines lower the surface to just
# the build output.
extension/
scripts/
